The best mobile firefighting game on Android, by far. The interior fire 
fighting is definitely the best part of the whole game. The flames are well 
done, the controls are simple and intuitive, and on the hard setting, the 
effects of heat stress and air consumption add a whole other level of 
urgency and excitement. There should however also be a medium difficulty 
setting which has air consumption and heat stress and response time limits, 
they should just be longer than the hard setting. The whole set up of 
hydrants and hoses before fighting the fire is a needless and boring step 
and should be removed though. The vehicle extrication and oil spill clean 
up leave a lot to be desired and need to be far more interactive. The drag 
and drop is just not exciting. It should be a first person view and fully 
interactive like the PC version. Still, overall, excellent game. Make the 
suggested corrections and it's worth five stars.

Fairly dissapointing having played the pc version, but definitely big room
